---
title: Pad Thai
description: Popular Thai stir-fried noodle dish with shrimp, tofu, and bold flavors.
---

Cook @noodles{200%g} according to package directions until tender, then drain and set aside.

Heat oil in a wok over high heat and stir-fry @garlic{3%cloves} and @shallot{2} until fragrant.

Add @shrimp{150%g} and @tofu{100%g} to the wok and cook until the @shrimp are pink, about 3 minutes.

Add the cooked @noodles{} to the wok along with @fish-sauce{2%tbsp}, @tamarind-paste{2%tbsp}, and @palm-sugar{1%tbsp}.

Toss everything together and push the noodles to one side of the wok.

Crack @egg{1} into the empty side of the wok and scramble it, then mix it throughout the noodles.

Top with crushed @peanut{50%g} and sliced @scallion{2} before serving.
